This is a fairly typical autotools package. In a nutshell, if you're using
a roughly Unix-ish environment:

    1.) For Ubuntu distros, you'll want to install the following dependencies:
    sudo apt update
    sudo apt install build-essential automake autoconf-archive \
                 libsdl2-dev git libtool libflac-dev perl \
                 pkgconf libutf8proc-dev
    2.) autoreconf -i

    3.) mkdir -p build

    4.) git pull

    5.) cd build && ../configure && make

    6.) ./schismtracker to run and happy trackin!

For more detailed instructions, peruse the files in the 'docs' directory.
